{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2151,"text":"By raising your hand,"},{"time":3592,"text":"how many of you know\nat least one person on the screen?"},{"time":8367,"text":"Wow, it's almost a full house."},{"time":10258,"text":"It's true, they are very famous\nin their fields."},{"time":12839,"text":"And do you know what\nall of them have in common?"},{"time":15858,"text":"They all died of pancreatic cancer."},{"time":18802,"text":"However, although it's very,\nvery sad this news,"},{"time":21334,"text":"it's also thanks to their personal stories"},{"time":24122,"text":"that we have raised awareness\nof how lethal this disease can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28267,"text":"It's become the third cause\nof cancer deaths,"},{"time":31667,"text":"and only eight percent of the patients\nwill survive beyond five years."},{"time":37217,"text":"That's a very tiny number,"},{"time":39160,"text":"especially if you compare it\nwith breast cancer,"},{"time":41940,"text":"where the survival rate\nis almost 90 percent."},{"time":45946,"text":"So it doesn't really come as a surprise"},{"time":48337,"text":"that being diagnosed\nwith pancreatic cancer"},{"time":50826,"text":"means facing an almost\ncertain death sentence."},{"time":54101,"text":"What's shocking, though,\nis that in the last 40 years,"},{"time":57771,"text":"this number hasn't changed a bit,"},{"time":60173,"text":"while much more progress has been made"},{"time":62301,"text":"with other types of tumors."},{"time":64552,"text":"So how can we make pancreatic cancer\ntreatment more effective?"},{"time":68659,"text":"As a biomedical entrepreneur,"},{"time":70589,"text":"I like to work on problems\nthat seem impossible,"},{"time":73632,"text":"understanding their limitations"},{"time":75717,"text":"and trying to find new,\ninnovative solutions"},{"time":78813,"text":"that can change their outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81035,"text":"The first piece of bad news\nwith pancreatic cancer"},{"time":83636,"text":"is that your pancreas is in the middle\nof your belly, literally."},{"time":87131,"text":"It's depicted in orange on the screen."},{"time":89990,"text":"But you can barely see it"},{"time":91661,"text":"until I remove all the other\norgans in front."},{"time":95093,"text":"It's also surrounded\nby many other vital organs,"},{"time":98113,"text":"like the liver, the stomach,\nthe bile duct."},{"time":101249,"text":"And the ability of the tumor\nto grow into those organs"},{"time":104686,"text":"is the reason why pancreatic cancer"},{"time":106732,"text":"is one of the most painful tumor types."},{"time":110295,"text":"The hard-to-reach location\nalso prevents the doctor"},{"time":113481,"text":"from surgically removing it,"},{"time":115224,"text":"as is routinely done\nfor breast cancer, for example."},{"time":118716,"text":"So all of these reasons leave\nchemotherapy as the only option"},{"time":122124,"text":"for the pancreatic cancer patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124745,"text":"This brings us to the second\npiece of bad news."},{"time":127579,"text":"Pancreatic cancer tumors have\nvery few blood vessels."},{"time":131624,"text":"Why should we care\nabout the blood vessel of a tumor?"},{"time":135434,"text":"Let's think for a second\nhow chemotherapy works."},{"time":138924,"text":"The drug is injected in the vein"},{"time":140837,"text":"and it navigates throughout the body\nuntil it reaches the tumor site."},{"time":145505,"text":"It's like driving on a highway,\ntrying to reach a destination."},{"time":150080,"text":"But what if your destination\ndoesn't have an exit on the highway?"},{"time":153989,"text":"You will never get there."},{"time":155642,"text":"And that's exactly the same problem"},{"time":157788,"text":"for chemotherapy and pancreatic cancer."},{"time":161119,"text":"The drugs navigate\nthroughout all of your body."},{"time":163988,"text":"They will reach healthy organs,"},{"time":166425,"text":"resulting in high toxic effect\nfor the patients overall,"},{"time":170256,"text":"but very little will go to the tumor."},{"time":172795,"text":"Therefore, the efficacy is very limited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176519,"text":"To me, it seems very counterintuitive\nto have a whole-body treatment"},{"time":181357,"text":"to target a specific organ."},{"time":183645,"text":"However, in the last 40 years,"},{"time":186121,"text":"a lot of money, research\nand effort have gone towards"},{"time":190469,"text":"finding new, powerful drugs\nto treat pancreatic cancer,"},{"time":194576,"text":"but nothing has been done\nin changing the way"},{"time":197011,"text":"we deliver them to the patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200397,"text":"So after two pieces of bad news,"},{"time":202047,"text":"I'm going to give you\ngood news, hopefully."},{"time":205806,"text":"With a collaborator at MIT"},{"time":207300,"text":"and the Massachusetts\nGeneral Hospital in Boston,"},{"time":210220,"text":"we have revolutionized\nthe way we treat cancer"},{"time":213157,"text":"by making localized\ndrug delivery a reality."},{"time":216974,"text":"We are basically parachuting you\non top of your destination,"},{"time":220984,"text":"avoiding your having to drive\nall around the highway."},{"time":223910,"text":"We have embedded the drug\ninto devices that look like this one."},{"time":229224,"text":"They are flexible enough\nthat they can be folded"},{"time":234437,"text":"to fit into the catheter,"},{"time":236383,"text":"so the doctor can implant it\ndirectly on top of the tumor"},{"time":240203,"text":"with minimally invasive surgery."},{"time":242603,"text":"But they are solid enough\nthat once they are positioned"},{"time":246397,"text":"on top of the tumor,"},{"time":248112,"text":"they will act as a cage."},{"time":249905,"text":"They will actually\nphysically prevent the tumor"},{"time":253080,"text":"from entering other organs,"},{"time":254779,"text":"controlling the metastasis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258459,"text":"The devices are also biodegradable."},{"time":260767,"text":"That means that once in the body,"},{"time":262541,"text":"they start dissolving,"},{"time":264450,"text":"delivering the drug only locally,\nslowly and more effectively"},{"time":269837,"text":"than what is done with the current\nwhole-body treatment."},{"time":273344,"text":"In pre-clinical study,\nwe have demonstrated"},{"time":276173,"text":"that this localized approach"},{"time":278196,"text":"is able to improve by 12 times\nthe response to treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282758,"text":"So we took a drug that is already known"},{"time":285559,"text":"and by just delivering it locally\nwhere it's needed the most,"},{"time":289414,"text":"we allow a response\nthat is 12 times more powerful,"},{"time":293087,"text":"reducing the systemic toxic effect."},{"time":297039,"text":"We are working relentlessly to bring\nthis technology to the next level."},{"time":301257,"text":"We are finalizing the pre-clinical testing"},{"time":304128,"text":"and the animal model required\nprior to asking the FDA for approval"},{"time":308231,"text":"for clinical trials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310969,"text":"Currently, the majority of patients\nwill die from pancreatic cancer."},{"time":316124,"text":"We are hoping that one day,"},{"time":317983,"text":"we can reduce their pain,\nextend their life"},{"time":321278,"text":"and potentially make pancreatic cancer"},{"time":324335,"text":"a curable disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326257,"text":"By rethinking the way we deliver the drug,"},{"time":329001,"text":"we don't only make it\nmore powerful and less toxic,"},{"time":332782,"text":"we are also opening the door\nto finding new innovative solutions"},{"time":337591,"text":"for almost all other impossible problems"},{"time":340330,"text":"in pancreatic cancer patients and beyond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343628,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344813,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}